The United Steelworkers said workers approved the previously announced buy-out of LTV Steel Co. 's bar division.
The new company will be called Republic Engineered Steels, the union said. 

The bar division employs 3,900 USW members and 1,000 salaried employees at eight locations. 

The union said 2,252 voted for the buy-out, while 1,184 voted against it.
USW will own 76% of company stock while management employees own 24%. 

